oc:kn_4c77075f a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing query performance, especially on large tables" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Filter early by pushing WHERE clauses as close to base tables as possible and using partition filters when available." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Early filtering reduces the amount of data processed in subsequent joins and aggregations, dramatically improving performance on partitioned tables." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_506036ea a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When queries have multiple logical steps" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use CTEs (WITH clauses) for readability — one CTE per logical transformation or data source, named descriptively (e.g., daily_signups, active_users)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "CTEs make complex queries readable, debuggable, and maintainable by breaking logic into named, composable steps." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6800e076 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before writing any SQL query" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always determine the SQL dialect before writing the query — supported dialects are PostgreSQL, Snowflake, BigQuery, Redshift, Databricks SQL, MySQL, SQL Server, DuckDB, and SQLite." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Dialect-specific syntax for dates, strings, windows, and performance features varies significantly across engines." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_7ebe1670 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting the final query to the user" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Query output includes: complete SQL in a code block, brief explanation of each CTE, performance notes, and modification suggestions for common variations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Providing context alongside the query ensures the user understands the logic, can verify correctness, and can adapt it for variations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_c0be803b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any SQL query" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use SELECT * in production queries — always specify only the needed columns." ;
    oc:hasRationale "SELECT * retrieves unnecessary data, increasing I/O, memory usage, and network transfer, and breaks when columns are added or reordered." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_fd60c333 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing subqueries in SQL" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid correlated subqueries when a JOIN or window function achieves the same result." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Correlated subqueries execute once per row of the outer query, leading to O(n²) performance instead of O(n) with a proper JOIN." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ff9795ee a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing subqueries and joins" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prefer EXISTS over IN for subqueries with large result sets; use appropriate JOIN types (INNER vs LEFT); be mindful of many-to-many exploding joins." ;
    oc:hasRationale "EXISTS short-circuits on first match while IN materializes the full set; wrong JOIN types produce incorrect or inflated results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

